---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Base title="Thanks — RECN">
  <Header />
  <main class="container" style="padding-top: 80px; padding-bottom: 80px; text-align: center;">
    <div class="accent-bar" style="width: 32px; margin: 0 auto var(--sp-md);"></div>
    <h1 style="font-size: 1.5rem; letter-spacing: 3px; margin-bottom: var(--sp-lg); text-transform: uppercase; font-family: var(--font-mono);">Thank you</h1>
    <div style="max-width: 480px; margin: 0 auto; text-align: left;">
      <p style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-md); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.8;">
        Really glad you're here.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-md); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.8;">
        I record a lot. Melodies, rough ideas, voice notes at odd hours. And I kept losing them — buried in a file manager, stuck in an app that wouldn't export right, or just gone because something didn't save properly. The ideas I cared about most were the ones I was most likely to lose.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-md); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.8;">
        RECN is my attempt to fix that. Not a product pitch — just a tool I needed and couldn't find. Something that records reliably, keeps everything on your device, and makes it easy to find that one idea from last Tuesday when you need it.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-md); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.8;">
        You're early to this, and I want to be honest about that. Things are moving fast, the design is still taking shape, and parts of it will change. But the thing that won't change is the reason it exists — no recording should ever be lost, and your ideas should always be yours.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-xl); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.8;">
        I'll keep you in the loop as it comes together. Thanks for caring about this before it's done.
      </p>
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--text-tertiary); letter-spacing: 1px;">
        — Shubham
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
